      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can this ever happen? I keep seeing conflicting comments and code throughout SkSL about our handling of assignable ternaries. The most recent thing I saw indicated that if the condition is literal, we\u0027ll bake the ternary down at IR conversion time. Other than that case, I thought we didn\u0027t allow them - most of our backends don\u0027t support them.",
      "revId": "00ec07941854d2c870a8a00e3583cd333c1df703",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
