      "writtenOn": "2021-02-12T14:38:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ternaries are not assignable in SkSL. This is probably dead code. I just verified that if we attempt to use a ternary as an Lvalue, we get\n\n\"error: 5: cannot assign to this expression\"\n\nUnlike GLSL, SkSL DOES allow ternaries to be assigned to if the ternary can be constant-folded away at IR generation time, and we have tests verifying that this works. This appears to be an intentional feature, along the lines of @if.",
